== Preparation ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash
and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Place @Butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small #microwave-safe bowl{};
microwave until melted, about ~{30%seconds}. Stir in
@Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup},
half the @Ranch Spice{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and
@pepper{}.

== Chicken ==

Pat @Chicken Breasts{12%oz} dry with paper towels and season all over with salt
and pepper. Place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Spread tops of chicken
breasts with @Mayonnaise{1%tsp} each (you'll use the rest later). Mound with
panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

== Potato Wedges ==

On a second baking sheet, toss potato wedges with a large drizzle of
@Olive Oil{}, remaining Ranch Spice, salt, and pepper. Roast potatoes on top
rack and chicken on middle rack until potatoes are golden brown and tender
and chicken is cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Green Beans and Spicy Mayo ==

When chicken and potatoes have 5 minutes left, pierce @Green Beans{6%oz} bag with
a fork; place bag on a #plate{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Transfer to a #medium bowl{} and toss with @Butter{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.
> No microwave? No problem! Steam beans in a small pot with a splash of water
> until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

In a second #small bowl{}, combine remaining @Mayonnaise{3%tbsp} and
@Sriracha{1%tsp} to taste.

== To Serve ==

Divide chicken, potato wedges, and green beans between plates. Serve with
spicy mayo on the side for dipping.